; Scans IVT entries for INT 0x80 through INT 0xBF looking for a loaded
; Sound Blaster 16 TSR. For each entry, reads the CS (segment) field;
; if CS:0000 contains the 'SB' signature (0x4253, i.e. bytes 0x53 'S',
; 0x42 'B'), the TSR has been found.
; Returns the TSR segment in AX, or 0 if no SB TSR is present.
; The 35-byte gap at 06CD–06EF is the never-executed success path.
sb_find_tsr_segment:   ; 10D1:06B4
